+---
+# Add safe `runs prune` cleanup
+
+## Goal
+
+Add `flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N>` so operators can
+delete old local run directories without risking active, incomplete, or
+unknown-state runs.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+- Run durability is journal-based only: `journal.jsonl` is replayed by
+  `src/state/run-journal.ts`.
+- Run directories live under `<workflowDir>/runs/<run-id>` via
+  `src/state/state.ts::getRunDir`.
+- Workflow locks live at `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock` via
+  `src/state/lock.ts::defaultLockPath` and contain the active `run_id`.
+- The CLI already routes subcommands in `src/cli.ts` and exposes shared
+  workflow resolution for commands that accept `--workflow`.
+
+### Current State
+
+- There is no local cleanup command for old run directories.
+- Users must delete runs manually, which can remove non-terminal runs,
+  locked runs, or directories whose journal cannot prove terminal state.
+- Existing tests cover journal replay and lock helpers, but not prune
+  selection.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Reuse `getRunDir`, journal replay, and lock helpers; do not duplicate path
+  or replay logic.
+- Treat missing or unreplayable journals as unknown and therefore skipped.
+- `--keep` must be a non-negative integer.
+- `--dry-run` must not delete anything.
+- No new dependencies.
+- Benchmark adaptation: variant-selection gate is non-interactive. Selected
+  variant is the state-service implementation below because it keeps CLI
+  parsing thin while making selection logic unit-testable.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] `FR-E83` is registered in the engine SRS and document index with
+      acceptance evidence. Acceptance tuple — FR-E83 + Test:
+      `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::FR-E83 prune keeps N newest terminal unlocked runs`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] Prune selection replays `journal.jsonl`, sorts by replayed run start
+      time, deletes only old terminal unlocked runs, and preserves the newest
+      `N`. Acceptance tuple — FR-E83 + Test:
+      `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::FR-E83 prune keeps N newest terminal unlocked runs`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] Non-terminal, locked, missing-journal, and unreplayable-journal runs are
+      skipped with per-run reasons. Acceptance tuple — FR-E83 + Tests:
+      `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::FR-E83 prune skips non-terminal and locked runs`,
+      `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::FR-E83 missing or unreplayable journals are unknown`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] `--keep 0` deletes every terminal unlocked run. Acceptance tuple —
+      FR-E83 + Test:
+      `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::FR-E83 keep zero deletes all terminal unlocked runs`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] `--dry-run` reports planned deletions and leaves files intact.
+      Acceptance tuple — FR-E83 + Test:
+      `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::FR-E83 dry-run deletes nothing`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] Bad `--keep` values fail clearly with a non-zero CLI path. Acceptance
+      tuple — FR-E83 + Test:
+      `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 parseRunsPruneArgs rejects bad keep`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] CLI help lists the `runs prune` command. Acceptance tuple — FR-E83 +
+      Test: `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 printUsage mentions runs prune`;
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+
+## Solution
+
+1. **State service.**
+   - Add `src/state/runs-prune.ts`.
+   - Export typed helpers:
+     - `parseNonNegativeInteger(raw, flagName)` for `--keep`.
+     - `selectRunsForPrune({ workflowDir, keep })`.
+     - `pruneRuns({ workflowDir, keep, dryRun })`.
+   - Enumerate `<workflowDir>/runs/`, ignore non-directories and `.lock`.
+   - For each run directory, compute the path with `getRunDir(runId,
+     workflowDir)`, replay via `replayRunJournal(runDir)`, and classify:
+     terminal when status is `completed`, `failed`, or `aborted`; otherwise
+     skip as non-terminal.
+   - Read lock with `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))`; if present,
+     skip the referenced `run_id` regardless of liveness or status. Missing
+     lock is normal; malformed lock should fail clearly.
+   - Sort terminal unlocked candidates by `state.started_at` descending,
+     keep the first `N`, delete the rest oldest-first.
+   - Missing/unreplayable journals become skipped runs with reason
+     `unknown state: <message>`.
+   - Deletion uses `Deno.remove(runDir, { recursive: true })`; dry-run only
+     returns the plan.
+
+2. **CLI wrapper.**
+   - In `src/cli.ts`, add `parseRunsPruneArgs(args)` and `runRuns(args)`.
+   - Support only `runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N> [--dry-run]`.
+   - Reject missing command, unknown flags, missing values, and bad `--keep`
+     with clear errors.
+   - Print a compact summary: deleted count, kept count, skipped count,
+     planned/deleted run IDs, and per-run skip reasons.
+   - Add the subcommand to `printUsage()` and import the state service.
+
+3. **RED tests.**
+   - Add `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts` with temp workflow fixtures and real
+     `RunJournalWriter` journals covering newest retention, non-terminal,
+     locked, missing/unreplayable journal, keep zero, and dry-run.
+   - Extend `src/cli_test.ts` for parser validation and help text.
+   - Run the focused tests and confirm they fail for missing exports.
+
+4. **GREEN implementation.**
+   - Implement the state service and CLI wrapper minimally to satisfy tests.
+   - Add `FR-E83` comments near the command/service entry points so the FR
+     coverage audit can map requirement to code.
+
+5. **Documentation.**
+   - Add `FR-E83` to `documents/requirements-engine.md`.
+   - Add the FR section to
+     `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md`.
+   - Update `documents/index.md` and SDS sections that describe `cli.ts`,
+     run journal replay, and workflow lock/run housekeeping.
+
+6. **Verification.**
+   - Run focused tests during RED/GREEN:
+     `deno task test --filter FR-E83`.
+   - Run the full gate: `deno task check`.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- A separate `runs list` command can expose inspection output; it is out of
+  scope here.
+
+## Review
+
+- Verdict: Approve.
+- Findings: none.
+- Evidence: `deno task check` passed.
